Nitrification rates were found significantly higher under exotic plantations as compared to native plantations (Fig. 6). But no significant differences were observed for nitrogen mineralization rates under exotic and native plantations (Fig. 6). However, it showed high variability under native plantations (3.62–8.59 mg kg-1 month-1) as compared to exotic plantations (5.01–5.35 mg kg-1 month-1).



